{ This is the most straightforward and direct approach. Black opens the long diagonal, the centre and the e-file while White's king is still uncastled. }
8. Nxd4
{ The natural and the only good recapture. Taking with a bishop only gives Black a tempo for development after  8.Bxd4?!  Re8  @@StartBracket@@attacking the pawn on e4@@EndBracket@@  9.Nd2  Bh6!  and after ...Nc6 next the bishop on d4 is short of squares - White will have to allow the wrecking of his structure after Be3 ...Bxe3,  fxe3 which gives Black a clear advantage. }
