{ Black achieved his goal and now threatens ...a5 to open the a-file. } 16. Bd3
{ Increasing control over the f5-square. The sacrifices on g4 don't work, Black's reaction to both is the same:  A@@EndBracket@@  16.Bxg4?!  hxg4  17.Nxg4  Nf6  18.Ne3  c6!  with the idea to activate the queen after ...Qb6.   B@@EndBracket@@  16.Nxg4?!  hxg4  17.Bxg4  Nf6  18.Bf5  c6!  with the same idea. }
16... a5 { Continuing the plan. } 17. b5
{ Unfortunately for him, White is forced to keep the queenside closed, but this kills any hope for him to achieve success there. He couldn't continue with  17.a3?  in view of  17...axb4  18.axb4  Rxa1  19.Qxa1  f5!  20.Rxf5  Rxf5  21.exf5  e4!  22.Bxe4  Qf6  and White loses a piece because of the pin on the long diagonal. }
17... Nc5
{ Now Black has an eternal knight on c5. His plan now is to execute the f5-break. }
18. Rb1
{ Removing the rook from the long diagonal, where it can become vulnerable after ...f5, exf5 ...e4! }
