{ Another useful waiting move for Black, putting the onus again on White. } 14.
h4 { This is an attempt to wait and not move the knight from e2. } 14... Kh7
{ Black continues the waiting game - Black waits for the knight from e2 to move in order to play ...e5 and ...Nd4. The king move also allows for a possible ...Bh6. }
15. Rd1 Nb6 { Attacking the vulnerable pawn on c4. } 16. Qa2
{ If  16.Nc1  Black gets his  16...e5  17.d5  Nd4  . } 16... Qe8
{ Getting away from the d-file and still waiting for White to decide what to do with his kingside. }
