10... a5
{ The standard move on the queenside, obtaining better control over the dark squares c5 and b4.  An interesting alternative is  10...c5!?  with a delayed Benoni structure. }
11. O-O
{ If White chases away the knight now it will help Black re-route it to c5 and start play in the centre after  11.a3  Na6  12.O-O  exd5  13.cxd5  Nc5  14.Qc2  c6  with counterplay against the pawn on e4 and active piece play. }
